  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Why risk seeing your plans fail just because you chose the wrong time to make a decisive move? Vultures, kings of opportunity live by this principle. Calculating, patient, intelligent and never impulsive, these Avians prefer to wait for the right moment to act and maximize their chances of success. Vultures hate losing or discovering that they are wrong even on trifles, and although they do not show it, they are extremely competitive. Unique among the Rapax, they are at ease in complex and nuanced social environments, where they find the ideal playing field for their plots. They do not hesitate to leverage their disturbing nature to manipulate others, and rarely are they themselves intimidated. They despise superficiality and naivety, considering them to be weaknesses, and tend not to have intimate personal relationships for the same reason: it is too easy for loved ones to become the currency of blackmail, and the last thing a Vulture wants is to offer<br />themselves to their opponents.</span> <br style=\"font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;line-height:normal;text-align:-webkit-auto;text-size-adjust:auto\" /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Increase in Ability Scores.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Your <span class=\"fontstyle0\">Charisma </span>score increases by 1 and your  <span class=\"fontstyle0\">Constitution </span>score increases by 2.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Age.</strong></em> </span>A Rapax reaches maturity around the age of 14 <span class=\"fontstyle0\">and is immediately considered independent. They have an average lifespan of around 60 years.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Speed. </strong></em></span></span>Your base speed on the ground is 20 feet, and your <span class=\"fontstyle0\">flight speed is 30 feet</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Size. </strong></em></span>A Vulture can reach a height of between 4 1/4 feet <span class=\"fontstyle0\">and 5 feet, and weigh between 65 lbs and 110 lbs. Your size is Medium.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Wild spirit.</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You have proficiency in the Survival skill.</span></p>\n<p><em><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Feared. </span></strong></em><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You have proficiency in the Intimidate ability.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.ZLta2Wjm3OsgNAk0]{Wings}</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.9ALHHLuQoSWQRqN4]{Prehensile Legs}</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[world.species-features.2zVRhhfSO8fMZWzt]{Acute Sight}</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.CsKP3pQcELPkECkY]{Discriminating Nose}</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[world.species-features.YSKG1QdtUq0r3jxt]{Brave}</span></p>\n<p>@Compendium[world.species-features.XXAgaQu5o3hNCwQA]{Rapax Claws}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[world.species-features.QuIdJAIbTc1h2oiV]{Rapax Peck}</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle3\"><em><strong>Instinct of Familia, Distance (Predator):</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle4\">“I can analyze situations while keeping at a distance”.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle4\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><em><strong>Instinct of Species, Treacherous:</strong></em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">“I hit the enemy when they are at their weakest.”</span> <br style=\"font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:normal;orphans:2;text-align:-webkit-auto;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-size-adjust:auto;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\" /></span></p>",
      "chat": "",
